+{"id":"frankenpandas-agabe","title":"fd90.94: README falsely says 'Rather than adding DType::Categorical variant' — variant exists in fp-types","description":"fd90.74-93 README audit. Line 397 reads: 'Rather than adding a DType::Categorical variant (which would require changing 52+ match arms across 4 crates), categoricals are implemented as a metadata layer on Series' — but the DType::Categorical variant DOES exist in crates/fp-types/src/lib.rs:75. It is matched at fp-types/src/lib.rs:179 + 441, fp-conformance lib.rs:5805, fp-io lib.rs:2060/2109/4217/9327, fp-columnar lib.rs:368. fp-frame lib.rs:126 explicitly comments: 'Series-level dtype reporting still surfaces DType::Categorical'. The architecture decision was actually: keep DType::Categorical as a *reportable identity* while physical storage is Int64 codes + CategoricalMetadata. Fix: rewrite line 397 to honestly describe the dual layer (variant exists for dtype-reporting; physical storage is Int64+metadata) instead of pretending the variant was avoided. Pure README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T09:21:20.049135962Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T09:22:27.295948694Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T09:22:27.293197796Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
